      • setActiveReason

        public void setActiveReason(de.ovgu.featureide.fm.core.explanations.fm.FeatureModelReason activeReason)
        Sets the currently active reason.

        Only does so in any of the following cases:

        • The new active reason is null. This makes it possible to reset the active reason.
        • The old active reason is null. After resetting, any new active reason is accepted.
        • The new active reason has a greater confidence than the old one. This means that, in case of graphically overlapping reasons, the greatest confidence is displayed.

        Overrides:
        setActiveReason in class ModelElementFigure
        Parameters:
        activeReason - the new active reason; null to reset
